Satellite images show us just how much Nevada's Lake Mead has dwindled in the past year. 

This week, the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation declared the first-ever water shortage on the Colorado River basin, including Lake Mead, the country’s largest reservoir.

The reservoir reached historically low water levels this summer, and is currently at 35% capacity.

This aerial view shows a flock of sheep in search of water in a lake that has dried up almost completely during the area's worst drought in a decade on Tuesday, Aug. 17, 2021, in Enna, Italy. Lake Pozzillo is the largest artificial lake in Sicily, but the lake has almost run out of water due to the enduring drought.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Weather Channel in Colorado River. May be an image of road and text that says 'Colorado River Drought to Lead to Unprecedented Measure'.

node.text:
For the first time ever, the federal government has declared a water shortage on the Colorado River.

The river that supplies water to some 40 million people across the West has seen water levels decline in some reservoirs as much as 50% in just five years.

As a result, mandatory water cuts will begin on Jan. 1 in Arizona and Nevada, and those restrictions could be expanded further if the drought worsens and water levels continue to drop.

It's yet another symptom of a warming world, climate scientists say.

Tap the link in our bio for the full story.

📸: Patrick T. Fallon/AFP via Getty Images

#ColoradoRiver #drought #ClimateChange #GlobalWarming

node.text:
This Sunday, Aug. 15, 2021, photo provided by U.S. Forest Service-Superior National Forest shows a rapidly growing wildfire in northeastern Minnesota that has prompted some evacuations, the U.S. Forest Service said Monday, Aug. 16, 2021. The fire was spotted around 3 p.m. Sunday near Greenwood Lake, about 15 miles southwest of Isabella, in the Superior National Forest.

By Tuesday, the fire had burned more than 3 square miles. Authorities said about 75 homes have been evacuated.

📸: Nick Petrack/Forest Service-Superior National Forest via AP

#GreenwoodFire #Minnesota #wildfire

node.text:
Firefighters are working hard to beat back the flames of the Dixie Fire which came within a few miles of Susanville, California, Lassen County’s seat, Monday into early Tuesday. The fire moved aggressively overnight due to heavy winds, and a red flag warning was issued for Tuesday until near midnight.

The blaze burned structures after jumping Highway 395 south of Janesville, California, on Monday night and evacuations were issued in the town. 
The Dixie Fire has burned more than 944 square miles and was still only 31% contained on Tuesday.

Click the link in our bio to see more powerful images of the largest fire burning in the U.S.

Photo by AP/Ethan Swope
